# Streamlit App Walkthrough (Piano Added)

## Summary
The app now includes a virtual piano interface overlay.

## Features
- **Piano Overlay**: A piano keyboard image is displayed at the bottom of the video feed.
- **Click Detection**: Point your index finger at a key and **curl it** (angle < 160 degrees) to simulate a press.
- **Feedback**:
    - The pressed key name ("C", "D", "E", etc.) appears on the video feed.
    - The key and finger angle are printed to the terminal for debugging.
    - The current angle of your index finger is displayed on screen to help you adjust your "clicking" motion.

## How to Run
```bash
./.venv/bin/streamlit run app.py
```
Open the URL shown in the terminal (usually http://localhost:8501 or 8502).
